152
00:10:10,080 --> 00:10:11,520
there's always a coffin

153
00:10:12,520 --> 00:10:14,360
left for one's own kin.

154
00:10:24,760 --> 00:10:25,760
Please restrain your grief,

155
00:10:25,760 --> 00:10:26,680
Miss Wang.

156
00:10:27,800 --> 00:10:28,680
Miss Wang.

157
00:10:30,120 --> 00:10:31,240
Why are you here?

158
00:10:31,640 --> 00:10:32,770
Aren't you here too?

159
00:10:33,200 --> 00:10:34,280
Coroner Li.

160
00:10:35,160 --> 00:10:36,880
The government notified me

161
00:10:37,080 --> 00:10:40,080
to claim my brother's body for burial.

162
00:10:40,240 --> 00:10:42,040
Is there any problem?

163
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:44,160
Today, I went to Changning Street,

164
00:10:44,480 --> 00:10:48,000
and happened to see Wanqing picking up new clothes at the fabric shop.

165
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:49,000
Thank you, boss.

166
00:10:49,640 --> 00:10:51,040
Please come again.

167
00:10:53,640 --> 00:10:55,040
Isn't this Wanqing?

168
00:10:55,480 --> 00:10:56,720
Long time no see.

169
00:10:57,320 --> 00:10:59,080
When she came out of the fabric shop,

170
00:10:59,080 --> 00:11:01,200
she happened to run into an acquaintance who said 'long time no see',

171
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:02,840
but she acted like she didn't know them,

172
00:11:02,840 --> 00:11:04,240
and reacted slowly.

173
00:11:05,120 --> 00:11:07,400
I learned from her acquaintance

174
00:11:07,440 --> 00:11:08,880
that she is a doctor.

175
00:11:09,280 --> 00:11:12,720
A while ago, Miss Wanqing had a burn on her shoulder.

176
00:11:12,800 --> 00:11:15,330
She was treated by the doctor you introduced.

177
00:11:15,520 --> 00:11:16,440
At that time,

178
00:11:17,160 --> 00:11:18,240
Wang Kang accompanied her,

179
00:11:18,240 --> 00:11:21,040
and they treated the wound together in the clinic.

180
00:11:21,560 --> 00:11:23,760
My brother was usually careless.

181
00:11:24,440 --> 00:11:28,920
That day, he spilled boiling water on Wanqing's shoulder,

182
00:11:28,960 --> 00:11:30,320
causing a burn,

183
00:11:30,880 --> 00:11:32,840
which left a scar afterwards.

184
00:11:33,720 --> 00:11:37,400
If Wanqing's parents knew about this,

185
00:11:38,400 --> 00:11:40,060
the marriage would be ruined.

186
00:11:41,440 --> 00:11:45,040
So we kept it a secret before.

187
00:11:50,920 --> 00:11:55,480
So she deliberately pretended not to know her.

188
00:11:58,400 --> 00:11:59,640
So Coroner Li,

189
00:12:00,160 --> 00:12:01,290
besides autopsies,

190
00:12:02,720 --> 00:12:04,720
is also in charge of investigation.

191
00:12:06,640 --> 00:12:07,680
Me?

192
00:12:09,080 --> 00:12:11,280
Autopsies and investigations

193
00:12:11,520 --> 00:12:13,840
are all for catching the killer as soon as possible,

194
00:12:13,840 --> 00:12:15,700
so the deceased can rest in peace.

195
00:12:17,760 --> 00:12:20,120
Who exactly killed my brother?

196
00:12:21,320 --> 00:12:22,920
We are still investigating.

197
00:12:23,080 --> 00:12:25,600
Currently, I also suspect Dongling.

198
00:12:25,960 --> 00:12:27,840
Both her parents have committed crimes

199
00:12:27,840 --> 00:12:29,400
and are now serving their sentences.

200
00:12:29,400 --> 00:12:31,440
It can't be ruled out that she wants to be the top courtesan,

201
00:12:31,440 --> 00:12:35,480
and became jealous of Qi Nianyao and Wanqing.

202
00:12:35,520 --> 00:12:36,880
Her parents' mistakes

203
00:12:37,480 --> 00:12:39,000
have nothing to do

204
00:12:39,040 --> 00:12:40,360
with whether she makes mistakes.

205
00:12:40,360 --> 00:12:41,640
My father said,

206
00:12:41,880 --> 00:12:42,880
if parents commit crimes,

207
00:12:42,880 --> 00:12:44,600
the chance of their children offending is very high.

208
00:12:44,600 --> 00:12:45,840
Who is your father?

209
00:12:51,280 --> 00:12:53,520
Anyway, we are still investigating.

210
00:12:53,840 --> 00:12:56,320
We won't miss a single clue.

211
00:12:58,600 --> 00:12:59,320
Yesterday,

212
00:13:00,280 --> 00:13:03,400
I noticed Wanqing's mother's eyes were a bit strange.

213
00:13:04,160 --> 00:13:05,820
She must be hiding something.

214
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:08,200
Why didn't you say so earlier?

215
00:13:08,240 --> 00:13:09,240
Let's go.

216
00:13:09,280 --> 00:13:10,560
Go. Hurry.

217
00:13:21,760 --> 00:13:22,720
We're late.

218
00:13:23,240 --> 00:13:24,370
She's already dead.

219
00:13:26,040 --> 00:13:27,570
What was her cause of death?

220
00:13:30,680 --> 00:13:34,340
The deceased is clutching a blue hairpin tightly in her left hand.

221
00:13:35,640 --> 00:13:36,760
Blood on the head,

222
00:13:37,040 --> 00:13:39,200
purple face, dark lips.

223
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:42,560
No pulse.

224
00:13:43,440 --> 00:13:45,800
Pupils slightly dilated.

225
00:13:47,560 --> 00:13:48,600
I want to ask,

226
00:13:49,080 --> 00:13:51,560
did the madam suffer from a heart condition before she died?

227
00:13:51,560 --> 00:13:54,360
Yes. She needed to take medicine all year round.

228
00:13:56,720 --> 00:14:00,380
Preliminary judgment: the deceased suddenly had a heart attack,

229
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:01,720
then became weak,

230
00:14:01,760 --> 00:14:03,680
and fell from the high platform,

231
00:14:04,280 --> 00:14:07,740
hitting the back of her head on the stone bench, causing death.

232
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:10,460
I want to see that hairpin.

233
00:14:17,160 --> 00:14:19,040
Take the body away first.

234
00:14:19,240 --> 00:14:20,120
Madam.

235
00:14:20,240 --> 00:14:20,960
Madam.

236
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:23,240
All right, don't get so worked up, Father.

237
00:14:23,240 --> 00:14:23,960
Don't worry.

238
00:14:23,960 --> 00:14:27,490
The authorities will definitely get to the bottom of this case.

239
00:14:27,760 --> 00:14:28,960
Come, sit down first.

240
00:14:29,360 --> 00:14:31,360
Sit down and tell me

241
00:14:32,280 --> 00:14:33,960
what exactly happened today.

242
00:14:35,320 --> 00:14:36,120
Around

243
00:14:37,360 --> 00:14:38,720
the hour of Shen.

244
00:14:40,720 --> 00:14:41,760
Madam

245
00:14:42,880 --> 00:14:45,960
took the dancers to the stage

246
00:14:47,120 --> 00:14:48,240
for rehearsal.

247
00:14:50,120 --> 00:14:51,880
After everyone was ready,

248
00:14:52,160 --> 00:14:54,160
Wanqing stood on the high platform,

249
00:14:54,400 --> 00:14:56,400
but she hesitated to make a move.

250
00:14:57,360 --> 00:15:00,240
Her mother knew something was wrong.

251
00:15:03,520 --> 00:15:04,560
All right.

252
00:15:04,840 --> 00:15:06,480
Let's stop practicing for now.

253
00:15:06,480 --> 00:15:08,480
Everyone go eat and touch up your makeup

254
00:15:08,480 --> 00:15:10,680
in preparation for tonight's performance.

255
00:15:10,680 --> 00:15:12,840
The dancers rehearsed the moves once,

256
00:15:13,280 --> 00:15:15,760
then returned to their rooms to eat and touch up,

257
00:15:15,760 --> 00:15:17,890
waiting for the evening performance.

258
00:15:19,320 --> 00:15:20,850
Unexpectedly at that time,

259
00:15:21,320 --> 00:15:23,800
she suddenly heard Wanrou's voice.

260
00:15:24,160 --> 00:15:25,400
Mother.

261
00:15:25,640 --> 00:15:27,560
Mother.

262
00:15:33,040 --> 00:15:34,240
Wanrou.

263
00:15:36,040 --> 00:15:37,240
Mother.

264
00:15:37,600 --> 00:15:39,330
She must have missed her so much

265
00:15:39,440 --> 00:15:42,440
that it created such an obsession and hallucination.

266
00:15:43,240 --> 00:15:44,000
Madam!

267
00:15:45,040 --> 00:15:45,760
Rou!

268
00:15:46,960 --> 00:15:47,400
Rou!

269
00:15:47,440 --> 00:15:47,840
Madam!

270
00:15:56,600 --> 00:15:57,440
Rou!

271
00:16:16,480 --> 00:16:18,400
By the time I reacted,

272
00:16:18,680 --> 00:16:20,400
it was too late.

273
00:16:24,080 --> 00:16:26,960
Then what is this hairpin about?

274
00:16:30,400 --> 00:16:31,520
This hairpin

275
00:16:32,040 --> 00:16:34,570
was originally given to my daughter by Madam.

276
00:16:35,200 --> 00:16:38,720
But she seemed to see Wanrou on stage,

277
00:16:39,760 --> 00:16:41,200
so she took it off.

278
00:16:41,880 --> 00:16:42,960
As far as I know,

279
00:16:43,560 --> 00:16:45,800
Wanqing has liked red since childhood.

280
00:16:46,040 --> 00:16:48,520
When performing on stage, she wore red shoes.

281
00:16:48,520 --> 00:16:51,400
Growing up, her boudoir was mainly decorated in red.

282
00:16:51,400 --> 00:16:53,460
But Wanrou was exactly the opposite.

283
00:16:53,800 --> 00:16:55,160
She liked blue.

284
00:16:55,480 --> 00:16:58,400
If you say Madam Ye wanted to give this blue hairpin

285
00:16:58,560 --> 00:17:01,290
to the non-existent Wanrou on the high platform,

286
00:17:02,200 --> 00:17:03,560
it makes sense.

287
00:17:04,319 --> 00:17:06,599
But for such an important performance today,

288
00:17:06,599 --> 00:17:07,680
Wanqing, you

289
00:17:08,319 --> 00:17:10,180
decided to change your red attire

290
00:17:11,520 --> 00:17:13,200
and wear a blue dress.

291
00:17:17,760 --> 00:17:20,599
So you are not Wanqing,

292
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:24,640
but Wanrou.

293
00:17:27,400 --> 00:17:30,200
No, impossible. How could she be Wanrou?

294
00:17:30,240 --> 00:17:31,240
How could that be?

295
00:17:31,840 --> 00:17:34,720
Father, look at what nonsense he's talking about.

296
00:17:34,960 --> 00:17:36,680
Wanrou has been dead for so long.

297
00:17:36,680 --> 00:17:37,600
Wait a minute.

298
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:39,860
I think his question makes sense.

299
00:17:43,560 --> 00:17:46,090
When all impossible options are eliminated,

300
00:17:46,640 --> 00:17:48,600
this only reasonable answer,

301
00:17:48,840 --> 00:17:50,240
no matter how absurd,

302
00:17:50,600 --> 00:17:51,760
must be the truth.

303
00:17:52,200 --> 00:17:54,360
No, it's impossible.

304
00:17:54,880 --> 00:17:56,760
She is my daughter, Wanqing.

305
00:18:00,040 --> 00:18:03,800
Parents can always notice slight changes in their children.

306
00:18:04,920 --> 00:18:06,240
Walking into your room

307
00:18:06,280 --> 00:18:09,040
and seeing that the dishes your mother made all have leeks,

308
00:18:09,040 --> 00:18:10,680
I assume you love to eat them.

309
00:18:11,120 --> 00:18:13,780
But when your mother cleaned the room, she found

310
00:18:13,880 --> 00:18:16,400
that the leeks in every dish had been picked out,

311
00:18:16,400 --> 00:18:17,930
which made her suspicious.

312
00:18:18,440 --> 00:18:20,880
realizing you had changed.

313
00:18:24,600 --> 00:18:25,960
And this suspicion

314
00:18:26,080 --> 00:18:27,920
grew stronger

315
00:18:28,520 --> 00:18:29,780
when she saw you again.

316
00:18:30,920 --> 00:18:33,520
When you came to the Guan residence in a blue dress,

317
00:18:33,520 --> 00:18:36,680
your mother knew it was Wanrou's favorite color.

318
00:18:36,920 --> 00:18:41,200
She immediately suspected that the person in front of her might not be Wanqing.

319
00:18:41,200 --> 00:18:42,640
When you stood on the stage

320
00:18:42,640 --> 00:18:44,240
and everyone was practicing the dance,

321
00:18:44,240 --> 00:18:45,680
you didn't move at all,

322
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:48,080
which made her even more certain.

323
00:18:48,360 --> 00:18:50,290
After all, Wanrou couldn't dance,

324
00:18:50,720 --> 00:18:52,920
so she couldn't replace Wanqing at all.

325
00:18:53,160 --> 00:18:54,960
So, after everyone left,

326
00:18:55,320 --> 00:18:57,200
she quietly went up the stage.

327
00:19:01,520 --> 00:19:02,280
Mother,

328
00:19:03,160 --> 00:19:04,280
why are you here?

329
00:19:06,200 --> 00:19:07,640
I came to see you.

330
00:19:09,160 --> 00:19:10,160
It's alright.

331
00:19:11,320 --> 00:19:12,360
Let's go.

332
00:19:13,280 --> 00:19:14,240
Wanrou.

333
00:19:28,720 --> 00:19:30,000
Growing up,

334
00:19:31,280 --> 00:19:32,920
you were neglected.

335
00:19:34,480 --> 00:19:35,840
For so many years,

336
00:19:36,640 --> 00:19:38,520
I didn't know where you were.

337
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:44,080
Now you can speak clearly,

338
00:19:45,240 --> 00:19:46,600
and you have grown up.

339
00:19:48,400 --> 00:19:51,360
Your father and I owe you so much.

340
00:19:56,640 --> 00:19:57,960
Stop it.

341
00:20:00,080 --> 00:20:03,240
It's not too late.

342
00:20:05,400 --> 00:20:06,640
There is still time.

343
00:20:09,560 --> 00:20:11,560
What's the point of saying this now?

344
00:20:11,920 --> 00:20:13,640
Will it make you feel better?

345
00:20:18,880 --> 00:20:20,080
When I was five,

346
00:20:20,680 --> 00:20:23,760
everyone laughed at me for stuttering.

347
00:20:23,800 --> 00:20:25,040
What were you doing?

348
00:20:26,320 --> 00:20:28,240
When I first performed on stage at seven,

349
00:20:28,240 --> 00:20:31,560
they laughed at my uncoordinated movements and being off-beat.

350
00:20:31,560 --> 00:20:33,320
What were you doing?

351
00:20:33,360 --> 00:20:38,480
When I was ten, I went to the river to kill myself in a fit of anger.

352
00:20:38,520 --> 00:20:39,880
Where were you?

353
00:20:39,920 --> 00:20:40,800
I...

354
00:20:41,880 --> 00:20:44,680
Do you think you can get my forgiveness

355
00:20:45,200 --> 00:20:47,060
just by saying you owe me too much?

356
00:21:08,080 --> 00:21:11,240
You pushed your own mother down with your own hands.

357
00:21:12,480 --> 00:21:14,120
You didn't die back then.

358
00:21:14,360 --> 00:21:16,440
Perhaps some family adopted you.

359
00:21:17,320 --> 00:21:19,440
The seeds of revenge took root

360
00:21:19,480 --> 00:21:21,540
and sprouted in your heart over time.

361
00:21:21,640 --> 00:21:24,040
So, you killed Wanqing,

362
00:21:24,560 --> 00:21:26,040
took her identity,

363
00:21:26,080 --> 00:21:28,360
and started your revenge plan.

364
00:21:28,800 --> 00:21:31,080
Wang Kang accidentally burned Wanqing,

365
00:21:31,240 --> 00:21:34,400
so he secretly asked a doctor to examine her and prescribe medicine.

366
00:21:34,400 --> 00:21:35,920
Today in the market,

367
00:21:35,960 --> 00:21:37,480
the doctor greeted you,

368
00:21:37,960 --> 00:21:40,600
but you seemed not to know him at all.

369
00:21:41,120 --> 00:21:42,400
It makes sense

370
00:21:42,720 --> 00:21:44,380
if you are a different person.

371
00:21:44,840 --> 00:21:45,800
So,

372
00:21:46,080 --> 00:21:48,640
you killed Wang Kang because...

373
00:22:13,720 --> 00:22:14,640
Who are you?

374
00:22:15,840 --> 00:22:19,000
Because he found no scars on your shoulder.

375
00:22:19,240 --> 00:22:21,040
You killed him to silence him.

376
00:22:21,280 --> 00:22:22,540
What about Qi Nianyao?

377
00:22:23,240 --> 00:22:26,720
Did Madam Ye plan to replace the top courtesan before she died?

378
00:22:27,880 --> 00:22:29,240
It must be you.

379
00:22:30,640 --> 00:22:31,920
That explains it.

380
00:22:32,080 --> 00:22:35,280
You took advantage of Qi Nianyao's fear of losing her title as the top courtesan,

381
00:22:35,280 --> 00:22:39,080
making her collude with you to stage a haunting.

382
00:22:39,800 --> 00:22:41,400
Have you thought it through?

383
00:22:41,800 --> 00:22:43,040
Do as I say.

384
00:22:43,760 --> 00:22:48,400
Make everyone think Wanrou came back to fight for the title of the top courtesan.

385
00:22:48,560 --> 00:22:50,920
Would Dongling still dare to take the position?

386
00:22:50,920 --> 00:22:52,680
After things settle down,

387
00:22:53,120 --> 00:22:54,640
my mother will realize

388
00:22:55,160 --> 00:22:58,760
who the real top courtesan is.

389
00:23:11,920 --> 00:23:12,720
Nianyao.

390
00:23:13,800 --> 00:23:15,360
Nianyao, what's wrong?

391
00:23:15,400 --> 00:23:16,730
What's wrong, Nianyao?

392
00:23:18,200 --> 00:23:19,040
Nianyao, what's wrong with you?

393
00:23:19,040 --> 00:23:20,320
Don't kill me!

394
00:23:20,360 --> 00:23:21,240
Don't kill me!

395
00:23:21,280 --> 00:23:23,000
Don't kill me!

396
00:23:27,320 --> 00:23:30,240
You instructed her to claim she saw ghosts multiple times

397
00:23:30,240 --> 00:23:32,720
and had her pretend to be possessed in her room,

398
00:23:32,720 --> 00:23:36,360
all to set the stage for the fire during the final performance.

399
00:23:36,880 --> 00:23:38,120
According to the plan,

400
00:23:38,120 --> 00:23:40,480
you smeared flammable oil on her costume.

401
00:23:40,600 --> 00:23:43,680
She would suddenly shout Wanrou's name during the performance

402
00:23:43,680 --> 00:23:45,280
and then ignite the costume.

403
00:23:45,400 --> 00:23:46,520
Wanrou is back!

404
00:23:46,560 --> 00:23:49,080
And you would be standing by with a basin of water,

405
00:23:49,080 --> 00:23:52,080
ready to put out the fire immediately. Wanrou is back!

406
00:23:54,560 --> 00:23:56,320
However, on the night of the incident,

407
00:23:56,320 --> 00:23:58,000
when she set herself on fire,

408
00:23:58,040 --> 00:23:59,320
you walked away.

409
00:23:59,400 --> 00:24:00,480
Because of this,

410
00:24:00,920 --> 00:24:02,320
when Nianyao was dying,

411
00:24:02,360 --> 00:24:04,320
she stared fixedly to the side.

412
00:24:06,240 --> 00:24:06,960
After that,

413
00:24:07,080 --> 00:24:08,440
you used the same trick

414
00:24:08,480 --> 00:24:09,800
to fake your own murder,

415
00:24:09,800 --> 00:24:12,330
which also reduced others' suspicion of you.

416
00:24:12,840 --> 00:24:15,170
From the moment you took Wanqing's place,

417
00:24:15,240 --> 00:24:17,440
your seemingly flawless plan

418
00:24:17,720 --> 00:24:19,840
slowly began to unfold.

419
00:24:20,160 --> 00:24:21,280
In your eyes,

420
00:24:21,600 --> 00:24:24,200
you can't tolerate anyone else being the top courtesan.

421
00:24:24,200 --> 00:24:25,730
The former Wanqing was one,

422
00:24:26,200 --> 00:24:28,480
and so is Qi Nianyao now.

423
00:24:29,560 --> 00:24:30,480
Nan Rongxiang.

424
00:24:31,040 --> 00:24:33,200
So you are covering up for your daughter.

425
00:24:33,200 --> 00:24:34,360
Covering up?

426
00:24:35,400 --> 00:24:37,880
My wife just fell to her death from the high platform.

427
00:24:37,880 --> 00:24:39,800
She is my only daughter.

428
00:24:40,680 --> 00:24:42,080
How dare you still argue?

429
00:24:42,480 --> 00:24:44,040
I'm not arguing.

430
00:24:44,320 --> 00:24:45,380
She really is my...

431
00:24:56,280 --> 00:24:57,960
After hearing your deduction,

432
00:24:57,960 --> 00:25:00,680
I almost thought I had become Wanrou.

433
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:04,520
Unfortunately, I am not.

434
00:25:05,280 --> 00:25:06,400
This dress

435
00:25:07,520 --> 00:25:10,520
was ordered by my mother at the tailor shop,

436
00:25:10,680 --> 00:25:12,280
and she chose the color too.

437
00:25:13,240 --> 00:25:14,600
If you don't believe me,

438
00:25:14,920 --> 00:25:17,120
you can ask the owner of the tailor shop.

439
00:25:17,160 --> 00:25:20,160
Do you dare to take off your clothes to check for scars?

440
00:25:56,400 --> 00:25:57,280
I guess

441
00:25:58,680 --> 00:25:59,880
you might say

442
00:26:00,920 --> 00:26:02,880
I deliberately burned myself.

443
00:26:04,520 --> 00:26:06,800
But Wanrou was born with a stutter.

444
00:26:06,840 --> 00:26:08,040
She was tone-deaf

445
00:26:08,120 --> 00:26:09,250
and couldn't dance.

446
00:26:09,840 --> 00:26:11,370
A stutter can be corrected,

447
00:26:11,480 --> 00:26:15,800
but a sense of dance and rhythm are innate and cannot be changed.

448
00:26:16,560 --> 00:26:17,760
Since Wanrou died,

449
00:26:18,600 --> 00:26:20,200
I have never danced again.

450
00:26:21,520 --> 00:26:22,360
Today,

451
00:26:23,440 --> 00:26:25,080
to prove that I am Wanqing,

452
00:26:26,920 --> 00:26:28,800
I will dance for all of you.

453
00:26:59,520 --> 00:27:02,360
Wearing gorgeous clothes,

454
00:27:02,600 --> 00:27:05,360
fingers tapping lightly,

455
00:27:05,840 --> 00:27:10,600
the past is no more.

456
00:27:12,240 --> 00:27:14,800
Foolishness and anger,

457
00:27:15,280 --> 00:27:18,080
half covering the face,

458
00:27:18,440 --> 00:27:23,320
endless affection is thick.

459
00:27:23,360 --> 00:27:24,800
She really is Wanqing.

460
00:27:25,280 --> 00:27:30,210
Her movements and dance are exactly the same as when she was a child. If there is no sorrow,

461
00:27:30,560 --> 00:27:31,520
It is her.

462
00:27:31,560 --> 00:27:36,520
burning longing surges.

463
00:27:44,200 --> 00:27:46,130
Could it be that I was really wrong?

464
00:27:47,520 --> 00:27:48,920
She really is Wanqing.

465
00:27:56,040 --> 00:27:58,720
Sis, I told you Jueming was a fraud.

466
00:27:58,840 --> 00:28:01,160
He gave an impassioned speech yesterday,

467
00:28:01,160 --> 00:28:03,400
and guess what? He went in the completely wrong direction.

468
00:28:03,400 --> 00:28:04,840
Freshly roasted chicken is here!

469
00:28:04,840 --> 00:28:05,700
Who wants some?

470
00:28:08,440 --> 00:28:09,570
Smells good, right?

471
00:28:09,640 --> 00:28:11,680
Silly boy, according to your analysis,

472
00:28:11,680 --> 00:28:14,410
we've been talking to ghosts these past two days.

473
00:28:15,920 --> 00:28:18,400
I don't think Nanrong Xiang is a good guy either.

474
00:28:18,400 --> 00:28:21,060
He clearly had something on his mind yesterday.

475
00:28:23,720 --> 00:28:26,120
Miss, here's your favorite chicken leg.

476
00:28:27,400 --> 00:28:28,260
I'm not hungry.

477
00:28:28,280 --> 00:28:31,720
Oh, there are only two legs on a chicken.

478
00:28:31,760 --> 00:28:33,480
One for you, and one for you.

479
00:28:34,280 --> 00:28:35,680
Ah, people just get

480
00:28:35,720 --> 00:28:37,680
irritable when they're hungry.

481
00:28:37,720 --> 00:28:41,560
Once you're full, everything looks better.

482
00:28:42,360 --> 00:28:45,160
Actually, I think that brat Jueming's

483
00:28:45,200 --> 00:28:47,200
analysis made a lot of sense.

484
00:28:47,800 --> 00:28:49,760
It's just that the conclusion

485
00:28:50,200 --> 00:28:52,080
doesn't quite add up.

486
00:28:52,520 --> 00:28:54,520
Then wasn't it all for nothing, Dad?

487
00:28:54,520 --> 00:28:56,850
Is this going to become another cold case?

488
00:28:59,480 --> 00:29:01,280
This chicken leg is really good.

489
00:29:01,680 --> 00:29:03,600
Oh, this chicken leg...

490
00:29:12,120 --> 00:29:15,000
Constable Su! Come over here.

491
00:29:23,000 --> 00:29:25,760
Why does this person look so much like Wanqing?

492
00:29:25,960 --> 00:29:28,480
But the name written here is Jiang Siyan.

